WHO WE ARE
We are Shinyfields Limited, a Cyprus company with registration no. HE 256351 and an address at
Avlonos 1, Maria House, 1075 Lefkosia, Cyprus, which operates websites itself and through certain

affiliates, including Skylum Software USA, Inc., a Nevada corporation and Photolemur, Inc., a Delaware
corporation (collectively, “Skylum”).
We operate the website at https://skylum.com/ ("Website"). This Website uses different types of cookies.
In the spirit of transparency, this Policy provides detailed information about why, how, and when we use
cookies on our Website.
WHAT A COOKIE IS
A cookie is a small text file stored by the website on your device and which contains information about
your browsing history, site usage etc.
Please note that the term "cookie" also covers other similar technologies for placing information on and
collecting from your device, such as local shared objects, flash cookies, beacons, tracking pixels, HTML5
(for internal storage).
WHY WE NEED COOKIES
We use cookies and other technologies to ensure everyone who uses the Website has the best possible
experience. For example, we use these cookies to hold session information as you navigate from page to
page within the Website, improve your experience, and track and analyze usage and other statistical
information.
If you elect not to activate cookies or disable cookies later, you may still visit our Website, but your ability
to use some features or areas of those offerings may be limited.
WHAT PERSONAL DATA WE COLLECT
We automatically collect technical information from cookies: IP address, geolocation, device type and
browser type, personal ID to monitor your session on the Website, information about the time of
interaction with the Website, as well as information about your interaction with the Website.
Please learn more about who we are, how to contact us, and how we process personal data in our
Privacy Policy.
HOW YOU CAN WITHDRAW YOUR CONSENT
By clicking ‘Accept All’, ‘Save Settings’ or ‘Decline All’ when using the website for the first time, you give
or refuse to give your consent for using marketing and statistical cookies. You may change or withdraw
your consent at any time by clicking ‘Change Choice on Cookies’ here or in the footer at the bottom of
each page of this website.
HOW YOU CAN TURN OFF COOKIES
You can generally deactivate the use of technical cookies through a functionality built into your web
browser. If you want to disable cookies, then you can find instructions for managing your browser settings
at these links:
Internet Explorer
Microsoft Edge
Mozilla Firefox
Google Chrome
Opera
Safari
Flash cookies
Apple
Android
Chrome, Android
WHAT COOKIES WE USE
Necessary
Strictly necessary cookies help make a website navigable by activating basic functions such as page
navigation and access to secure website areas. Without these cookies, the website would not be able to
work properly.
Functional
Functional cookies make it possible to save information that changes the way the website appears or acts. For instance your preferred language or region.
Statistical
Statistical cookies help the website owner understand how visitors interact with the website by collecting and reporting information.
Marketing
Marketing cookies are used to track visitors across websites. The intention is to display ads that are relevant and interesting to the individual user and thus more valuable for publishers and third-party advertisers.
AMENDMENTS
This Policy may be amended or updated from time to time to reflect changes in our practices with respect
to the processing of personal data, or changes in applicable laws or regulations.
We encourage you to read this Policy carefully, and to regularly check this page to review any changes
we might make in accordance with the terms of this Policy. We will inform you in case of any significant
changes which may impact you.
This Policy was last modified on [2 September 2022].
